Package: brainconnectome
Title: Brain Connectome Analysis (R Interface to Python Package)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Riley", "Harper", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Sean", "Shen", role = "aut"),
    person("Yinyu", "Yao", role = "aut")
    )
Description: R interface to the brain-connectome Python package for analyzing
    brain structural and functional connectomes from the Human Connectome Project.
    Uses reticulate to call Python functions, providing a seamless R experience
    while leveraging the Python implementation.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.26)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.9), brain-connectome Python package
